text: {'data': 'The properties of coatings based on Desmodur BL 4265 SN blocked polyisocyanate can be influenced, as with two - component polyurethane systems, by the degree of crosslinking and the choice of the polyol. The cure time and temperature required are also dependent upon the choice of coreactant. Combining Desmodur BL 4265 SN blocked polyisocyanate with hydroxyl - functional polyesters such as Desmophen 670 BA gives films with high flexibility and hard - ness. The cure rate can be varied by catalysis with - out adverse effects on storage. Crosslinking with polyamines or amides may result in limited storage stability. In coil coating systems, adequate crosslink - ing may be achieved without catalysis at 465 ºF peak metal temperature ( P.M.T. ) . With the addition of 1 % dibutyl tin dilaurate ( DBTDL ) based on solid resin, a crosslinking temperature of 435 ºF P.M.T. is possible. Thermal yellowing may occur at temperatures above 320 ºF ( 160 ℃ ) , depending on the baking time and the polyol used. Testing in Florida indicates that Desmo - dur BL 4265 SN blocked polyisocyanate provides excellent weather stability comparable to Desmodur N 3390 A BA/SN polyisocyanate.', 'label': []}
label: irrelevant
